## Definitions

For the purposes of this License, the following terms shall have the meanings set forth below:

**"License"**
Refers to this document — the IdeaNax Open License, Version 1.0 (INOL-1.0), including all its terms, conditions, and appendices.

**"Licensor"**
Refers to IdeaNax, the original author, creator, and copyright holder of the Work, including any authorized representatives or successors of IdeaNax.

**"You" / "Your"**
Refers to the individual person, company, organization, government entity, or legal entity that exercises rights granted by this License. "Your" is the possessive form of the same.

**"Work"**
Refers to the original software, source code, object code, documentation, configuration files, data, design assets, libraries, APIs, or any other material or content made available by IdeaNax under this License. The Work is identified by the presence of the INOL-1.0 license notice in its source files, header, or accompanying documentation.

**"Source Form"**
Refers to the human-readable form of the Work, including but not limited to source code, documentation source, configuration files, and build scripts.

**"Object Form"**
Refers to any machine-executable or compiled form of the Work resulting from transformation or translation of Source Form, including but not limited to compiled binaries, bytecode, generated documentation, and processed data.

**"Modified Work"**
Refers to any work derived from or based upon the original Work in which one or more files have been added, altered, removed, renamed, or otherwise changed from the original version of the Work. This includes, but is not limited to: forks, adaptations, translations, ports, extended versions, and derivative works.

**"Distribution"**
Refers to making a copy of the Work or Modified Work available to any third party, whether in Source Form, Object Form, as part of a product, service, library, platform, or in any other form of transmission or publication, whether or not such copy is made available for a fee.

**"Contribution"**
Refers to any original work of authorship submitted to the Licensor for inclusion in the Work, including bug fixes, improvements, documentation updates, or any other modification. By submitting a Contribution, the contributor grants IdeaNax and all downstream users the rights defined in this License.

**"Contributor"**
Refers to the Licensor and any other individual or legal entity that submits a Contribution to the Work.

**"Patent Claims"**
Refers to all patent claims owned or controlled by a Contributor that are necessarily infringed by the use or combination of that Contributor's Contribution with the Work as submitted.

**"Trademark"**
Refers to the name "IdeaNax," its logo, stylized wordmarks, product names, domain names, and any other identifiers that identify the source of goods or services provided by IdeaNax.

**"End User"**
Refers to a person or entity that uses or interacts with the Work or any product built upon the Work, without themselves distributing or modifying the Work.

**"Prominent Notice"**
Refers to an attribution statement placed in a location that is reasonably visible and accessible to users of the Work or Modified Work, such as in a README file, an About page, source file headers, documentation, or an in-app credits section.

