## Distribution Conditions

When distributing the Work or any Modified Work, You must satisfy **all** of the following conditions:

### 5.1 — Include This License

You must include a complete, unmodified copy of this License (IdeaNax Open License 1.0) with every distribution of the Work or Modified Work. This copy may be included:

- As a file named `LICENSE`, `LICENSE.md`, `LICENSE.txt`, or `COPYING` in the root of the distribution.
- As an appendix or section in the product's documentation.
- As a reference to the canonical online URL where this License is permanently published (e.g., `https://ideanax.com/licenses/INOL-1.0`), provided the text is freely accessible.

### 5.2 — Include Attribution Notice

You must include a prominent attribution notice crediting IdeaNax in your distribution. See Section 6 for detailed attribution requirements and templates.

### 5.3 — Include Modification Notice (if applicable)

If You are distributing a Modified Work, You must include a modification notice. See Section 7 for detailed modification notice requirements.

### 5.4 — Carry Forward This License

Any distribution of the Work or Modified Work must use the IdeaNax Open License 1.0 as the governing license for the portions derived from the Work. You must not distribute the Work or Modified Work under a license that:

- Removes or overrides the attribution requirements of this License.
- Removes or overrides the patent termination provisions of this License.
- Claims exclusive ownership of IdeaNax's original contributions.

You **may** distribute the Work as part of a larger combined work under different license terms, provided that the terms of this License are clearly preserved and communicated for the portions derived from the Work.

### 5.5 — Binary and Object Form Distribution

If You distribute the Work or Modified Work in Object Form (compiled binaries, executables, packages, container images, etc.), You must either:

- Include the Source Form of the Work or Modified Work alongside the Object Form, or
- Provide a written offer, valid for at least three (3) years, to provide the Source Form upon request.

### 5.6 — Network Distribution

If You deploy the Work or Modified Work as part of a network-accessible service (e.g., a SaaS platform, web application, API service, or cloud service), You are not required to distribute the Source Form solely by virtue of providing network access. However, attribution requirements under Section 6 still apply in a prominent location of your service (e.g., About page, Terms of Service, in-app credits, or documentation).

