## Attribution Requirements

Proper attribution to IdeaNax is the cornerstone of this License. When distributing the Work or Modified Work, You must satisfy **all** of the following attribution requirements:

### 6.1 — Mandatory Attribution Statement

All distributions of the Work or Modified Work must include the following attribution statement in a **Prominent Notice** location:

> *"This product includes or is derived from work originally created by **IdeaNax** (https://ideanax.com), used under the IdeaNax Open License 1.0 (INOL-1.0)."*

### 6.2 — Attribution in Documentation

If the Work or Modified Work includes user-facing documentation (README, user manual, help files, wiki, website, etc.), the attribution statement must appear in at least one of the following locations:

- The introduction or overview section of the documentation.
- A dedicated "Credits," "Acknowledgements," or "Third-Party Licenses" section.
- The footer or header of a documentation website.

### 6.3 — Attribution in Software Applications

If the Work or Modified Work is distributed as part of a software application with a graphical user interface, the attribution statement must appear in at least one of the following:

- An "About" dialog, screen, or page accessible to end users.
- An in-app credits section.
- The application's splash screen or startup message.
- The application's official website or app store description.

### 6.4 — Attribution in Source Code

If You distribute the Work or Modified Work in Source Form, the attribution statement must appear in one or more of the following:

- A `LICENSE` or `NOTICE` file in the root of the repository or archive.
- A comment block in the primary entry-point file (e.g., `main.py`, `index.js`, `App.java`).
- A `CREDITS.md` or `ACKNOWLEDGEMENTS.md` file.

### 6.5 — Attribution in Commercial Products

If the Work is incorporated into a commercial product or service that is sold, licensed, or monetized, the attribution statement must appear in the product's commercial documentation, packaging, or sales materials, in addition to satisfying the requirements of Sections 6.1 through 6.4.

### 6.6 — Attribution Format

The attribution statement must be human-readable and written in the primary language of the product's documentation or user interface. It must include:

- The name **IdeaNax** (exact spelling, capitalization preserved).
- A link or reference to `https://ideanax.com`.
- A reference to the IdeaNax Open License 1.0 or INOL-1.0.

The attribution statement must not be hidden, obfuscated, displayed in a font size smaller than the body text of the surrounding content, or placed in a location that is unreasonably difficult for users to find.

