## Modification Requirements

If You create and distribute a Modified Work, You must comply with all requirements in Section 5 and Section 6, plus the following additional requirements:

### 7.1 — Clear Modification Statement

You must include a clear, written statement in your distribution indicating that modifications have been made to the original Work. This statement must be placed in the `README`, `NOTICE`, `CHANGELOG`, or a similarly prominent file, and must include:

- A statement that the work was derived from IdeaNax's original Work.
- A list or description of the files or components that were modified.
- A brief description of the nature of the modifications.
- The date or date range during which the modifications were made.
- The name or identifier of the party who made the modifications (You or your organization).

**Example modification statement:**

```
This product was modified from the original IdeaNax Work.

Original Work: [Name of original Work]
Original Author: IdeaNax (https://ideanax.com)
License: IdeaNax Open License 1.0 (INOL-1.0)

Modified by: [Your Name / Organization]
Date of Modification: [Date or date range]

Summary of Modifications:
- Modified files: [list of files]
- Nature of changes: [brief description]
```

### 7.2 — Preservation of Original Attribution

When distributing a Modified Work, You must not remove or alter the original attribution notices that credit IdeaNax, even if those notices appear in files that You have modified. You may add additional attribution notices alongside the original ones, but the original IdeaNax attribution must remain intact and unaltered.

### 7.3 — Distinction from Original Work

Your Modified Work must not be presented, named, or marketed in a way that could confuse users into believing it is the official, unmodified Work produced by IdeaNax. If You use a name similar to the original Work, You must clearly indicate that your version is a modified derivative, not the official release.

### 7.4 — No False Endorsement

You must not imply or suggest that IdeaNax has reviewed, endorsed, approved, or sponsored your Modified Work, unless You have obtained explicit prior written permission from IdeaNax to make such a representation.

