You must not remove, alter, obscure, or modify any copyright notice, license header, attribution statement, or disclaimer that appears in the Work or any documentation associated with the Work.

### 9.2 — No False Attribution

You must not falsely claim to be the original creator of the Work or any substantial part of it. You must not misrepresent the origin, authorship, or provenance of the Work.

### 9.3 — No License Override

You must not distribute the Work or Modified Work under a license that eliminates or conflicts with the attribution requirements, patent provisions, or other core terms of this License.

### 9.4 — No Trademark Use Without Permission

You must not use the IdeaNax name, logo, or any trademark associated with IdeaNax to:

- Name your product, organization, or service in a way that implies it is created or endorsed by IdeaNax.
- Market or promote your product as an official IdeaNax product.
- Create the impression that your Modified Work is the official, Licensor-approved version of the Work.

Permitted trademark use includes: truthful statements that your product is based on or derived from IdeaNax's Work, and standard attribution notices required by this License.

For any trademark use beyond what is expressly permitted, you must obtain prior written permission from IdeaNax at: legal@ideanax.com.

### 9.5 — No Patent Retaliation

If You initiate patent litigation (including a cross-claim or counterclaim) against any person or entity alleging that the Work constitutes patent infringement, all patent licenses granted to You under this License shall terminate immediately as of the date such litigation is filed.

